Standard and Poor's Corp said it hasupgraded approximately two billion dlrs of securities for theWilliams Cos. and its related entities.    S and P said recent sales of non-regulated oil and gas,coal, fertilizer, and telecommunications assets significantlyreduce business risk. With 900 mln dlrs of proceeds availableto reduce debt, the financial profile should also improve.    Among issues upgraded were Williams' debentures, raised toBB-plus from BB-minus and Williams Natural Gas Co's debenturesand preferred stock to BBB-minus from BB-plus. NorthwestPipeline Corp issues also were upgraded. Reuter&#3;